WEBVTT

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:00.800 align:middle line:90%


00:00:00.800 --> 00:00:02.940 align:middle line:90%
[WHOOSH]

00:00:02.940 --> 00:00:04.900 align:middle line:90%


00:00:04.900 --> 00:00:07.840 align:middle line:90%
[GAIA JINGLE PLAYING]

00:00:07.840 --> 00:00:09.310 align:middle line:90%


00:00:09.310 --> 00:00:11.770 align:middle line:90%
[MUSIC PLAYING]

00:00:11.770 --> 00:00:14.560 align:middle line:84%
>> There's pain in life,
and there's suffering.

00:00:14.560 --> 00:00:15.760 align:middle line:90%
Pain we can't avoid.

00:00:15.760 --> 00:00:18.010 align:middle line:90%
Suffering is optional.

00:00:18.010 --> 00:00:20.470 align:middle line:84%
And one of the great
reasons we suffer

00:00:20.470 --> 00:00:22.810 align:middle line:84%
is because we believe
there's reasons for why

00:00:22.810 --> 00:00:25.540 align:middle line:90%
things happen as they do.

00:00:25.540 --> 00:00:29.155 align:middle line:84%
But life is not reasonable,
and it never will be.

00:00:29.155 --> 00:00:32.550 align:middle line:90%
[MUSIC PLAYING]

00:00:32.550 --> 00:00:40.330 align:middle line:90%


00:00:40.330 --> 00:00:43.690 align:middle line:10%
Whether we realize it or
not, we're all essentially

00:00:43.690 --> 00:00:47.800 align:middle line:10%
anchored in a belief
that God is on our side

00:00:47.800 --> 00:00:51.250 align:middle line:10%
or that justice
should work for me

00:00:51.250 --> 00:00:54.220 align:middle line:10%
and that if we've not done
anything bad, then nothing bad

00:00:54.220 --> 00:00:55.660 align:middle line:10%
should ever happen to me.

00:00:55.660 --> 00:01:00.370 align:middle line:84%
We want this world to
be a reasonable place,

00:01:00.370 --> 00:01:04.239 align:middle line:84%
that we want life to
be some kind of force

00:01:04.239 --> 00:01:05.750 align:middle line:90%
that we can reason with.

00:01:05.750 --> 00:01:08.110 align:middle line:10%
And where did our
love of reason come

00:01:08.110 --> 00:01:12.220 align:middle line:10%
from, and why is it important
to understand its origin?

00:01:12.220 --> 00:01:14.100 align:middle line:90%
[MUSIC PLAYING]

00:01:14.100 --> 00:01:16.750 align:middle line:84%
You know, the threads of
our allegiance to reason,

00:01:16.750 --> 00:01:21.250 align:middle line:84%
versus virtue or the left or
the right side of our brain,

00:01:21.250 --> 00:01:23.470 align:middle line:84%
really goes all the way
back to ancient Greece,

00:01:23.470 --> 00:01:26.140 align:middle line:90%
to Plato and Aristotle.

00:01:26.140 --> 00:01:29.320 align:middle line:84%
They debated how this
universe was structured.

00:01:29.320 --> 00:01:33.940 align:middle line:84%
Was it more valuable to pursue
logic, or reason, or virtue,

00:01:33.940 --> 00:01:35.320 align:middle line:90%
or beauty?

00:01:35.320 --> 00:01:38.350 align:middle line:84%
Was beauty and virtue
the way of order,

00:01:38.350 --> 00:01:40.360 align:middle line:90%
or was it logic or reason?

00:01:40.360 --> 00:01:43.858 align:middle line:84%
What would serve a
person more to know

00:01:43.858 --> 00:01:45.150 align:middle line:90%
as they lived in this universe?

00:01:45.150 --> 00:01:46.690 align:middle line:84%
And they debated
this because they

00:01:46.690 --> 00:01:50.530 align:middle line:84%
were teaching their students
to live in this universe,

00:01:50.530 --> 00:01:53.680 align:middle line:90%
to live in this world.

00:01:53.680 --> 00:01:56.920 align:middle line:84%
One was a more intuitive
path, and the other one

00:01:56.920 --> 00:01:59.770 align:middle line:84%
was more reasonable, as
if, somehow or other,

00:01:59.770 --> 00:02:04.360 align:middle line:84%
there could be found an ultimate
logical, reasonable system

00:02:04.360 --> 00:02:08.530 align:middle line:84%
through which we could
finally, finally, finally deal

00:02:08.530 --> 00:02:11.410 align:middle line:84%
with the gods, deal
with the heavens,

00:02:11.410 --> 00:02:17.890 align:middle line:84%
in order to stop sudden chance
from happening in our lives--

00:02:17.890 --> 00:02:21.220 align:middle line:84%
that we could, somehow or
other, stop unreasonable things

00:02:21.220 --> 00:02:22.750 align:middle line:90%
from happening.

00:02:22.750 --> 00:02:24.910 align:middle line:84%
So you see, going
back, we've always

00:02:24.910 --> 00:02:29.440 align:middle line:84%
wanted the universe to
somehow be an organized place.

00:02:29.440 --> 00:02:33.920 align:middle line:84%
It's just that it never
listened to us, ever.

00:02:33.920 --> 00:02:36.780 align:middle line:84%
So now what does all this have
to do with defying gravity?

00:02:36.780 --> 00:02:40.056 align:middle line:90%
[MUSIC PLAYING]

00:02:40.056 --> 00:02:43.340 align:middle line:90%


00:02:43.340 --> 00:02:46.100 align:middle line:84%
We're going to come into this
through the Old Testament,

00:02:46.100 --> 00:02:50.600 align:middle line:84%
my very favorite book,
which is the Book of Job.

00:02:50.600 --> 00:02:53.520 align:middle line:84%
And I think most people
know the story of Job.

00:02:53.520 --> 00:02:56.750 align:middle line:10%
You know, the righteous man,
and the devil came up to Yahweh

00:02:56.750 --> 00:02:59.300 align:middle line:10%
and said, I could tempt
your most righteous man.

00:02:59.300 --> 00:03:02.310 align:middle line:10%
And of course, Yahweh says to
the devil, well, have at it.

00:03:02.310 --> 00:03:03.380 align:middle line:90%
Give it your best shot.

00:03:03.380 --> 00:03:04.770 align:middle line:90%
[SOUND OF LIGHTNING]

00:03:04.770 --> 00:03:08.990 align:middle line:84%
So the devil kills Job's
crops, and he starts

00:03:08.990 --> 00:03:10.550 align:middle line:90%
just destroying his life.

00:03:10.550 --> 00:03:13.608 align:middle line:84%
And every single time
something bad happens to Job,

00:03:13.608 --> 00:03:15.650 align:middle line:84%
his neighbors would come
over and they would say,

00:03:15.650 --> 00:03:18.320 align:middle line:84%
you must have done
something terrible,

00:03:18.320 --> 00:03:21.770 align:middle line:84%
otherwise a reasonable god
wouldn't do this to you.

00:03:21.770 --> 00:03:24.260 align:middle line:84%
And he'd say, but I
didn't do anything.

00:03:24.260 --> 00:03:26.130 align:middle line:90%
I didn't do anything.

00:03:26.130 --> 00:03:29.060 align:middle line:84%
And finally, Job's wife
dies, his crops are gone,

00:03:29.060 --> 00:03:32.900 align:middle line:84%
he's lost everything--
absolutely everything.

00:03:32.900 --> 00:03:35.120 align:middle line:10%
But then, of course,
the neighbors

00:03:35.120 --> 00:03:39.050 align:middle line:10%
want job to confess something
because this is how they've

00:03:39.050 --> 00:03:42.270 align:middle line:10%
structured their universe.

00:03:42.270 --> 00:03:44.450 align:middle line:10%
And if Job didn't
do anything wrong,

00:03:44.450 --> 00:03:49.850 align:middle line:10%
it meant that this whimsical
god could suddenly strike

00:03:49.850 --> 00:03:51.740 align:middle line:10%
something in their life too.

00:03:51.740 --> 00:03:55.520 align:middle line:84%
So they had to find Joe
guilty of something, you see.

00:03:55.520 --> 00:03:59.870 align:middle line:84%
So then an angel comes up to Job
and says, maybe it's you, Job.

00:03:59.870 --> 00:04:01.610 align:middle line:90%
Maybe it's your attitude.

00:04:01.610 --> 00:04:03.710 align:middle line:90%
Maybe God should talk to you.

00:04:03.710 --> 00:04:07.190 align:middle line:84%
So he says, prepare
to talk to God.

00:04:07.190 --> 00:04:09.710 align:middle line:84%
This is the most
wonderful line, I

00:04:09.710 --> 00:04:13.510 align:middle line:84%
think, in the whole
Old Testament,

00:04:13.510 --> 00:04:17.839 align:middle line:84%
where Yahweh says to
Job, where were you

00:04:17.839 --> 00:04:21.200 align:middle line:84%
when I laid the foundations
of this universe?

00:04:21.200 --> 00:04:23.860 align:middle line:10%
Where were you when
I named the beasts,

00:04:23.860 --> 00:04:27.500 align:middle line:10%
and I ordered the
birds, and I structured

00:04:27.500 --> 00:04:29.960 align:middle line:10%
the planets and the galaxies?

00:04:29.960 --> 00:04:32.480 align:middle line:84%
And here's Job,
who, by this time,

00:04:32.480 --> 00:04:36.350 align:middle line:84%
is just this little piece
of sand on a grand beach.

00:04:36.350 --> 00:04:38.210 align:middle line:10%
Now, can you imagine--

00:04:38.210 --> 00:04:45.020 align:middle line:10%
as I say to my students, think
of your way saying this to you.

00:04:45.020 --> 00:04:48.140 align:middle line:84%
When you are looking at your
life and you're thinking,

00:04:48.140 --> 00:04:51.140 align:middle line:84%
how could this happen
to me, whatever it is

00:04:51.140 --> 00:04:52.610 align:middle line:90%
that you're thinking about--

00:04:52.610 --> 00:04:54.230 align:middle line:84%
how could my life
be such a mess,

00:04:54.230 --> 00:04:56.390 align:middle line:90%
how could this happen to me?

00:04:56.390 --> 00:04:59.060 align:middle line:10%
There must be a reason
in God in this universe

00:04:59.060 --> 00:05:00.140 align:middle line:10%
because look at us.

00:05:00.140 --> 00:05:02.330 align:middle line:10%
We're reasoning creatures.

00:05:02.330 --> 00:05:04.616 align:middle line:10%
So there must be
a reasoning God.

00:05:04.616 --> 00:05:07.292 align:middle line:90%
[MUSIC PLAYING]

00:05:07.292 --> 00:05:08.190 align:middle line:90%


00:05:08.190 --> 00:05:11.880 align:middle line:84%
Our love affair with reason
has scaffolded our thinking out

00:05:11.880 --> 00:05:14.560 align:middle line:90%
of the soul and into the mind.

00:05:14.560 --> 00:05:18.240 align:middle line:84%
And in so doing, it shifted the
way we related to everything,

00:05:18.240 --> 00:05:20.010 align:middle line:90%
including our health.

00:05:20.010 --> 00:05:22.200 align:middle line:84%
The underlying
premise is that if we

00:05:22.200 --> 00:05:25.140 align:middle line:84%
can excavate these
reasons, then our lives

00:05:25.140 --> 00:05:26.910 align:middle line:90%
will return to normal.

00:05:26.910 --> 00:05:29.190 align:middle line:84%
We will revive our
health and be just as

00:05:29.190 --> 00:05:32.190 align:middle line:84%
vibrant as we were
before, but the truth

00:05:32.190 --> 00:05:34.290 align:middle line:90%
is this rarely happens.

00:05:34.290 --> 00:05:37.180 align:middle line:84%
We cannot reason our
way back to health.

00:05:37.180 --> 00:05:41.370 align:middle line:84%
You cannot reason with illness
or crisis because crises are

00:05:41.370 --> 00:05:47.060 align:middle line:84%
the most unreasonable events
that will ever happen to you.

00:05:47.060 --> 00:05:54.300 align:middle line:84%
Well, and with that
in mind, every time--

00:05:54.300 --> 00:05:58.530 align:middle line:84%
we say, I need a reason for
why things happen as they do.

00:05:58.530 --> 00:06:00.090 align:middle line:90%
No you don't.

00:06:00.090 --> 00:06:01.600 align:middle line:90%
No you don't.

00:06:01.600 --> 00:06:02.640 align:middle line:90%
I can give you a reason.

00:06:02.640 --> 00:06:04.050 align:middle line:90%
Anyone can give you a reason.

00:06:04.050 --> 00:06:10.150 align:middle line:84%
But the fact is, however
the universe is ordered,

00:06:10.150 --> 00:06:12.370 align:middle line:90%
this is what's true.

00:06:12.370 --> 00:06:14.480 align:middle line:84%
You are not the center
of the universe.

00:06:14.480 --> 00:06:17.890 align:middle line:84%
We are, none of us, the
center of the universe.

00:06:17.890 --> 00:06:21.280 align:middle line:84%
And there are reasons for
why things happen as they do,

00:06:21.280 --> 00:06:26.180 align:middle line:84%
but I'm not sure we can
understand those reasons.

00:06:26.180 --> 00:06:29.610 align:middle line:90%
[MUSIC PLAYING]

00:06:29.610 --> 00:06:32.167 align:middle line:90%


00:06:32.167 --> 00:06:33.750 align:middle line:84%
I'm going to give
you a reason why you

00:06:33.750 --> 00:06:35.160 align:middle line:90%
can't understand the reason.

00:06:35.160 --> 00:06:38.370 align:middle line:84%
And you know, people are
really comfortable these days

00:06:38.370 --> 00:06:40.680 align:middle line:84%
with reincarnation,
with thinking

00:06:40.680 --> 00:06:44.790 align:middle line:84%
that maybe it's stress or it's
toxic relationship with someone

00:06:44.790 --> 00:06:47.400 align:middle line:90%
came from a past life.

00:06:47.400 --> 00:06:50.210 align:middle line:84%
They don't have any
problem with that.

00:06:50.210 --> 00:06:52.210 align:middle line:90%
Let me tell you something.

00:06:52.210 --> 00:06:54.240 align:middle line:10%
Some of the readings I've done--

00:06:54.240 --> 00:06:57.670 align:middle line:10%
not a lot, but some--

00:06:57.670 --> 00:07:03.310 align:middle line:10%
I recognized that a
pattern that I was seeing--

00:07:03.310 --> 00:07:06.640 align:middle line:10%
let's call it an influencer--

00:07:06.640 --> 00:07:13.880 align:middle line:10%
was not from a past life, but
from a life yet to be lived--

00:07:13.880 --> 00:07:15.560 align:middle line:10%
yet to be lived--

00:07:15.560 --> 00:07:20.180 align:middle line:10%
that the reason a person
was having a particular type

00:07:20.180 --> 00:07:26.200 align:middle line:10%
of challenge was
that it had something

00:07:26.200 --> 00:07:32.240 align:middle line:10%
to do with something yet to
happen in the physical world.

00:07:32.240 --> 00:07:34.720 align:middle line:90%
So that's number one.

00:07:34.720 --> 00:07:41.190 align:middle line:84%
And so that's a factor that
doesn't even occur to us.

00:07:41.190 --> 00:07:44.670 align:middle line:84%
We are comfortable thinking
in terms of our history,

00:07:44.670 --> 00:07:49.200 align:middle line:84%
but we have yet to even
begin to comprehend.

00:07:49.200 --> 00:07:53.910 align:middle line:84%
We are living in a
world of simultaneity,

00:07:53.910 --> 00:07:57.680 align:middle line:90%
but we can't comprehend that.

00:07:57.680 --> 00:08:01.240 align:middle line:84%
We still think in
terms of, there

00:08:01.240 --> 00:08:07.990 align:middle line:84%
must be one reason for every
one thing that happens to us.

00:08:07.990 --> 00:08:12.610 align:middle line:84%
And yet, there is karma, and
there's lives yet to be lived,

00:08:12.610 --> 00:08:15.350 align:middle line:84%
and there's influences of
other people in our lives.

00:08:15.350 --> 00:08:17.980 align:middle line:84%
And if all of
that's true, how can

00:08:17.980 --> 00:08:23.140 align:middle line:84%
there just be one reason for
why things happen as they do?

00:08:23.140 --> 00:08:27.190 align:middle line:84%
So you see we can't
have things both ways.

00:08:27.190 --> 00:08:35.510 align:middle line:84%
And because we can't possibly
comprehend the true reasons

00:08:35.510 --> 00:08:38.799 align:middle line:90%
why things happen as they do--

00:08:38.799 --> 00:08:39.799 align:middle line:90%
I'll tell you something.

00:08:39.799 --> 00:08:43.190 align:middle line:10%
The need for a
reason is actually

00:08:43.190 --> 00:08:48.760 align:middle line:10%
a psychic weight that prevents
the miraculous from happening.

00:08:48.760 --> 00:08:53.390 align:middle line:84%
I'll give you an example
that defies gravity.

00:08:53.390 --> 00:08:57.500 align:middle line:84%
The college I went to, it
was founded by French nuns

00:08:57.500 --> 00:09:00.710 align:middle line:90%
a long time ago in the 1840s.

00:09:00.710 --> 00:09:06.860 align:middle line:84%
And the woman who founded
it was, not so long ago,

00:09:06.860 --> 00:09:10.226 align:middle line:84%
canonized the eighth
American saint.

00:09:10.226 --> 00:09:12.130 align:middle line:90%
[MUSIC PLAYING]

00:09:12.130 --> 00:09:15.910 align:middle line:84%
So here's the miracle that
got her into sainthood.

00:09:15.910 --> 00:09:18.400 align:middle line:90%
This one man was blind.

00:09:18.400 --> 00:09:22.420 align:middle line:90%
He had cataracts over his eyes.

00:09:22.420 --> 00:09:26.200 align:middle line:84%
And he couldn't see
anything except, like,

00:09:26.200 --> 00:09:30.070 align:middle line:90%
5% light coming through.

00:09:30.070 --> 00:09:35.010 align:middle line:84%
He knew about the sisters
praying for this canonization.

00:09:35.010 --> 00:09:37.510 align:middle line:84%
On the way back
from an appointment

00:09:37.510 --> 00:09:40.270 align:middle line:84%
with his ophthalmologist,
he said to his wife,

00:09:40.270 --> 00:09:42.130 align:middle line:90%
would you stop at that church?

00:09:42.130 --> 00:09:43.930 align:middle line:90%
And I just want to say a prayer.

00:09:43.930 --> 00:09:48.290 align:middle line:84%
He goes to a painting of
Sister Garen and said,

00:09:48.290 --> 00:09:51.640 align:middle line:84%
I know you don't know me
and I'm not a Catholic,

00:09:51.640 --> 00:09:57.660 align:middle line:84%
but if you have any influence,
I'd appreciate your help.

00:09:57.660 --> 00:10:00.460 align:middle line:90%
That was his prayer.

00:10:00.460 --> 00:10:03.390 align:middle line:84%
[SIGHS] And the
next day he woke up,

00:10:03.390 --> 00:10:05.010 align:middle line:84%
and the cataracts
were still there,

00:10:05.010 --> 00:10:08.550 align:middle line:84%
but he had 20/20 vision,
which he still has.

00:10:08.550 --> 00:10:12.210 align:middle line:84%
And he went to his
ophthalmologist, who said,

00:10:12.210 --> 00:10:14.380 align:middle line:90%
this is impossible.

00:10:14.380 --> 00:10:15.390 align:middle line:90%
This can't happen.

00:10:15.390 --> 00:10:16.860 align:middle line:90%
But it did.

00:10:16.860 --> 00:10:18.780 align:middle line:90%
Classic miracle speak.

00:10:18.780 --> 00:10:21.090 align:middle line:90%
Here's the thing.

00:10:21.090 --> 00:10:23.880 align:middle line:84%
A miracle is something
that's totally beyond reason.

00:10:23.880 --> 00:10:25.860 align:middle line:90%
The nature of God--

00:10:25.860 --> 00:10:28.540 align:middle line:84%
and by the way, I'm
going to say this.

00:10:28.540 --> 00:10:33.160 align:middle line:84%
I am not politically correct,
and I have no use for that.

00:10:33.160 --> 00:10:35.130 align:middle line:84%
So when I say God,
if you need to hear

00:10:35.130 --> 00:10:39.150 align:middle line:84%
Goddess, whatever you need
to hear, throw it in there.

00:10:39.150 --> 00:10:41.730 align:middle line:84%
But I say god, and
that's the end of it.

00:10:41.730 --> 00:10:42.570 align:middle line:90%
Are we clear?

00:10:42.570 --> 00:10:43.370 align:middle line:90%
OK.

00:10:43.370 --> 00:10:45.130 align:middle line:90%
Keep going.

00:10:45.130 --> 00:10:47.830 align:middle line:84%
A woman came into
one of my workshops.

00:10:47.830 --> 00:10:50.380 align:middle line:84%
She had a slow
growing brain tumor.

00:10:50.380 --> 00:10:55.630 align:middle line:84%
And by this time, I was teaching
the work of Teresa of Ávila

00:10:55.630 --> 00:10:58.150 align:middle line:90%
and "The Interior Castle."

00:10:58.150 --> 00:11:02.400 align:middle line:84%
And I would lead people
on prayers for healing.

00:11:02.400 --> 00:11:07.000 align:middle line:84%
And what I told them, as
I'm going to tell you now--

00:11:07.000 --> 00:11:09.020 align:middle line:84%
and this is the nature
of sacred power,

00:11:09.020 --> 00:11:12.550 align:middle line:84%
and it's the nature of
healing beyond reason--

00:11:12.550 --> 00:11:15.200 align:middle line:90%
beyond reason.

00:11:15.200 --> 00:11:19.770 align:middle line:84%
And one of the
things about prayer

00:11:19.770 --> 00:11:24.220 align:middle line:84%
is you have to be willing to
let unreasonable things happen

00:11:24.220 --> 00:11:28.010 align:middle line:90%
within you and around you.

00:11:28.010 --> 00:11:33.530 align:middle line:84%
And the way of your soul is to
get you to become unreasonable.

00:11:33.530 --> 00:11:39.110 align:middle line:84%
So you can see that there
is an inherent clash in you

00:11:39.110 --> 00:11:41.610 align:middle line:84%
because you want people
to be reasonable.

00:11:41.610 --> 00:11:42.890 align:middle line:90%
You want life to be--

00:11:42.890 --> 00:11:45.500 align:middle line:84%
and it's not
reasonable, controlling.

00:11:45.500 --> 00:11:51.120 align:middle line:84%
But in fact, when your back is
against the wall with illness,

00:11:51.120 --> 00:11:56.220 align:middle line:84%
the only way out of a terminal
illness, in so many cases,

00:11:56.220 --> 00:12:01.380 align:middle line:84%
is something crazy and
unreasonable, like a miracle.

00:12:01.380 --> 00:12:04.390 align:middle line:84%
So here's this woman
in my workshop,

00:12:04.390 --> 00:12:07.690 align:middle line:84%
and she just said
this prayer, whatever

00:12:07.690 --> 00:12:11.560 align:middle line:84%
it takes, whatever it
takes, which is really

00:12:11.560 --> 00:12:14.070 align:middle line:90%
quite an unreasonable prayer.

00:12:14.070 --> 00:12:17.310 align:middle line:10%
It means whatever it takes.

00:12:17.310 --> 00:12:20.330 align:middle line:10%
She came to a later
workshop of mine.

00:12:20.330 --> 00:12:24.620 align:middle line:84%
And she came up to me and she
said, my brain tumor is gone.

00:12:24.620 --> 00:12:28.850 align:middle line:84%
And she said, I want you to know
that I came to your workshop.

00:12:28.850 --> 00:12:33.110 align:middle line:84%
And she said it was
spreading, it was malignant,

00:12:33.110 --> 00:12:36.080 align:middle line:84%
and I was given a
few months to live.

00:12:36.080 --> 00:12:38.440 align:middle line:84%
And she said, and
I decided I'm going

00:12:38.440 --> 00:12:40.580 align:middle line:84%
to give the most
unreasonable prayer ever,

00:12:40.580 --> 00:12:42.090 align:middle line:90%
which is whatever it takes.

00:12:42.090 --> 00:12:44.360 align:middle line:84%
And somehow, in that
moment, she said

00:12:44.360 --> 00:12:46.543 align:middle line:90%
I felt grace comes through.

00:12:46.543 --> 00:12:48.910 align:middle line:90%
[MUSIC PLAYING]

00:12:48.910 --> 00:12:54.850 align:middle line:84%
